，他的父亲Thomas Wale17岁，母亲Mary Crown15岁。他于1551年2月11日与Joane Cooper在英国英格兰艾可拉德文特结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1550年在他的家乡享年30岁。"},"hr":{"29 NOV 1520–1550":"29. studenog 1520.–1550.","1520–1550":"1520.–1550.","1521–1600":"1521–1600","1521–1604":"1521–1604","1571–1626":"1571–1626","1535–1592":"1535–1592","1503–1563":"1503–1563","1505–1525":"1505–1525.","1550":"1550.","1571":"1571","1592":"1592","1525":"1525.","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1600":"1600","29 NOV 1520":"29. studenog 1520.","1521":"1521","1520":"1520.","1563":"1563","about 1535":"oko 1535.","1505":"1505","1626":"1626","1604":"1604","Dutton, Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Dutton Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Engleska, United Kingdom","England":"Engleska, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, Engleska, United Kingdom","Westhall, Suffolk, England":"Westhall, Suffolk, England"},"cs":{"29 NOV 1520–1550":"29. listopadu 1520–1550","1520–1550":"1520–1550","1521–1600":"1521–1600","1521–1604":"1521–1604","1571–1626":"1571–1626","1535–1592":"1535–1592","1503–1563":"1503–1563","1505–1525":"1505–1525","1550":"1550","1571":"1571","1592":"1592","1525":"1525","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1600":"1600","29 NOV 1520":"29. listopadu 1520","1521":"1521","1520":"1520","1563":"1563","about 1535":"okolo 1535","1505":"1505","1626":"1626","1604":"1604","Dutton, Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Dutton Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom","England":"Anglie, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, Anglie, United Kingdom","Westhall, Suffolk, England":"Westhall, Suffolk, Anglie"},"da":{"29 NOV 1520–1550":"29. november 1520–1550","1520–1550":"1520–1550","1521–1600":"1521–1600","1521–1604":"1521–1604","1571–1626":"1571–1626","1535–1592":"1535–1592","1503–1563":"1503–1563","1505–1525":"1505–1525","1550":"1550","1571":"1571","1592":"1592","1525":"1525","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1600":"1600","29 NOV 1520":"29. november 1520","1521":"1521","1520":"1520","1563":"1563","about 1535":"omkring 1535","1505":"1505","1626":"1626","1604":"1604","Dutton, Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Dutton Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom","Westhall, Suffolk, England":"Westhall, Suffolk, England"},"nl":{"29 NOV 1520–1550":"29 november 1520–1550","1520–1550":"1520–1550","1521–1600":"1521–1600","1521–1604":"1521–1604","1571–1626":"1571–1626","1535–1592":"1535–1592","1503–1563":"1503–1563","1505–1525":"1505–1525","1550":"1550","1571":"1571","1592":"1592","1525":"1525","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1600":"1600","29 NOV 1520":"29 november 1520","1521":"1521","1520":"1520","1563":"1563","about 1535":"circa 1535","1505":"1505","1626":"1626","1604":"1604","Dutton, Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Dutton Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Essex, England":"Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Westhall, Suffolk, England":"Westhall, Suffolk, England"},"en":{"29 NOV 1520–1550":"29 November 1520–1550","1520–1550":"1520–1550","1521–1600":"1521–1600","1521–1604":"1521–1604","1571–1626":"1571–1626","1535–1592":"1535–1592","1503–1563":"1503–1563","1505–1525":"1505–1525","1550":"1550","1571":"1571","1592":"1592","1525":"1525","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1600":"1600","29 NOV 1520":"29 November 1520","1521":"1521","1520":"1520","1563":"1563","about 1535":"about 1535","1505":"1505","1626":"1626","1604":"1604","Dutton, Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Dutton Bassett, Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom","Westhall, Suffolk, England":"Westhall, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wale","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Anglo-Norman French personal name <i>Wale</i>, ancient Germanic <i>Walo</i> (Old French <i>Gal</i>, <i>Galon</i>, a source of   Gale   and   Gallon  ), from an ancient Germanic personal name <i>Walo</i>, either a byname meaning ‘foreigner’ (see   Wallace  ), or else a short form of various compound names with this first element.","English: nickname for a well-liked person, from Middle English <i>wale</i> ‘goodly, noble, excellent’ (originally meaning ‘choice’), or a nickname from Middle English <i>wale</i> (Old English <i>wealh</i>) ‘foreigner, Welshman’.","English: topographic name for someone who lived near an embankment, from Middle English <i>wale</i> ‘ridge, bank’ (Old English <i>walu</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Gale","meanings":["English: nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>gal</i>, <i>gale</i>, <i>galle</i> ‘cock, cockerel’.","English: habitational name from a minor place called with either Middle English <i>gale</i>, <i>gagel</i> (Old English <i>gagel</i>) ‘bog myrtle’, or with Middle English <i>gale</i> ‘fishery paying dues to the lord’ (Old English <i>gafol</i> ‘tax’?) such as Gale in Bickington (Devon) and The Gale, the name of a fishery in Ham and Stone (Gloucestershire).","English: topographic name from Middle English <i>gale</i>, <i>gail</i> (Old Norse <i>geil</i>) ‘ravine, narrow lane’, or a habitational name from a place so named such as Gale in Littleborough, Rochdale (Lancashire), or possibly High Gale in Tatham or Tunstall (Lancashire). With the sense ‘narrow lane’ it is found in several street names in medieval York."]},{"name":"Whale","meanings":["English:","nickname from Middle English <i>whal</i>, <i>hwal</i>, <i>wale</i> ‘whale’ (Old English <i>hwæl</i>), a term that was used to denote any large fish or marine mammal, including the walrus, grampus, and porpoise. The nickname may refer to a rolling gait or to size and weight.","variant of   Wale   or   Wall  ."]},{"name":"Wallman","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ernst, Frieda, Fritz, Kurt.","English (Cambridgeshire): either an occupational name meaning meaning ‘servant of <i>Wale</i>’ (see   Wale  ), or a topographic name for someone who lived by a wall (see   Wall  ).","Swedish: ornamental name composed of (a variant of) the elements <i>vall</i> ‘grassy bank’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’."]},{"name":"Walson","meanings":["English: from the Anglo-Norman French personal name   Wale   + <i>-son</i>, meaning ‘son of Wale’."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Wale was born on 29 November 1520, in Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Wale, was 17 and his mother, Mary Crown, was 15. He married Joane Cooper on 11 February 1551, in Radwinter, Essex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1550, in his hometown, at the age of 30."},"et":{"29 NOV 1520–1550":"29. november 1520–1550","1520–1550":"1520–1550","1521–1600":"1521–1600","1521–1604":"1521–1604","1571–1626":"1571–1626","1535–1592":"1535–1592","1503–1563":"1503–1563","1505–1525":"1505–1525","1550":"1550","1571":"1571","1592":"1592","1525":"1525","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1600":"1600","29 NOV 1520":"29. november 1520","1521":"1521","1520":"1520","1563":"1563","about 1535":"umbes 1535","1505":"1505","1626":"1626","1604":"1604","Dutton